2026-02-25T20:06:17.0727650Z     [33m        multi-format string, e.g. 'Iteration %d -- %10.5f', in which[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0728246Z     [33m        case `delimiter` is ignored. For complex `X`, the legal options[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0728467Z     [33m        for `fmt` are:[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0728628Z     [33m[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0729109Z     [33m        * a single specifier, ``fmt='%.4e'``, resulting in numbers formatted[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0729433Z     [33m          like ``' (%s+%sj)' % (fmt, fmt)``[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0729906Z     [33m        * a full string specifying every real and imaginary part, e.g.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0730271Z     [33m          ``' %.4e %+.4ej %.4e %+.4ej %.4e %+.4ej'`` for 3 columns[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0730756Z     [33m        * a list of specifiers, one per column - in this case, the real[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0731185Z     [33m          and imaginary part must have separate specifiers,[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0731796Z     [33m          e.g. ``['%.3e + %.3ej', '(%.15e%+.15ej)']`` for 2 columns[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0732057Z     [33m    delimiter : str, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0732401Z     [33m        String or character separating columns.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0732647Z     [33m    newline : str, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0732986Z     [33m        String or character separating lines.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0733227Z     [33m    header : str, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0733672Z     [33m        String that will be written at the beginning of the file.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0733920Z     [33m    footer : str, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0734317Z     [33m        String that will be written at the end of the file.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0734565Z     [33m    comments : str, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0735256Z     [33m        String that will be prepended to the ``header`` and ``footer`` strings,[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0735732Z     [33m        to mark them as comments. Default: '# ',  as expected by e.g.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0735976Z     [33m        ``numpy.loadtxt``.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0736253Z     [33m    encoding : {None, str}, optional[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0736758Z     [33m        Encoding used to encode the outputfile. Does not apply to output[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0737274Z     [33m        streams. If the encoding is something other than 'bytes' or 'latin1'[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0737784Z     [33m        you will not be able to load the file in NumPy versions < 1.14. Default[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0738002Z     [33m        is 'latin1'.[39;49;00m
2026-02-25T20:06:17.0738172Z     [33m[39;49;00m
